Ecuador signed four loans from theInterAmerican Development Bank (IADB) totaling 280 mln dlrs,the IADB said.    Ecuador's finance minister, Domingo Cordovez, and IADBPresident Antonio Ortiz Mena, signed the loans after the IADB'sannual meeting here.    A 57 mln dlr loan is for urban development, 80 mln dlrs forindustrial programs, 96 mln dlrs for highway rehabilitationand 46 mln for farm research. Reuter&#3;